 clusters would be lost from the sample. Allowing for redshift\nevolution of the form $(1+z)^{2.5}$ increases the incompleteness to $5.6\\pm1.0$\npercent. Improved constraints on the evolution of the cluster radio galaxy LF\nrequire a larger cluster sample extending to higher redshift.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 17 May 2016 20:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-25"}
