ADACS) and the\nelectronics. The Drag-Free CubeSat will be the result of the combined efforts\nof Stanford, University of Florida, KACST and NASA and will be the first\ndrag-free mission with an optical readout and the first GRS designed within the\nlimits of a 3U small satellite. In the first section, this paper briefly\nupdates on the main characteristics and systems of the project. Particular\nemphasis is then given to the recently designed housing, its expected\nperformance and the open issues.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 May 2016 09:41:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-19"}
